parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rust and leaks in the fuel system can cause fuel to leak into the trunk compartment, leading to a strong gas odor in the cabin and potentially causing a fire hazard.
symptoms: Strong gas odor in the cabin
fuel leaks into the trunk compartment
rusted fuel neck and fuel tank.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump can cause the engine to stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded in traffic.
symptoms: Engine shuts off while coasting to a stop
engine coughs and sputters
engine restarts briefly before stalling again
engine only runs after allowing it to rest for 10-15 minutes
car stalls in heavy traffic.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine camshaft position sensor can cause the engine to violently shake and stall, leading to a loss of control and increased risk of accidents, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: The engine violently shakes
the engine stalls
the vehicle loses power
the vehicle only starts after waiting periods of 10-15 minutes
the vehicle only runs for 5-10 minutes before the engine issue recurs
the "Check Engine" light illuminates
the PO012 engine code is displayed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The faulty ECU software can cause the engine to malfunction, leading to a loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The "Check Engine" light illuminates
the PO012 engine code is displayed
the engine runs rough
the engine stalls.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the manual transmission can cause the vehicle to stall or lock in neutral, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The transmission is hard shifting
the vehicle shudders and stalls
the transmission locks in neutral
the vehicle will not move
the failure occurs only in first gear
the failure occurs when the engine is cold
the failure does not occur as often when the vehicle is warm.
